<br>
Haste effects vary in how much faster they make you, and there is some controversy over the best way to measure it. Most commonly, players measure this as % increase in Attacks/time, though some people measure as % Delay reduction. Be careful of any haste% claims on items, as the % is useless without knowing how it was measured.<br>
<br>
The FBSS gives a 21% increase in Attacks/time - which means a 21% increase in damage output. However, it takes up an armor slot while giving no AC. Therefore, it is not generally the haste item of choice for Monks - though some like it since it occupies a different slot than the Monk epic (unlike the more popular Silver Chitin Hand Wraps, which give 22% plus 10 AC and a few stat bonuses).<br>
<br>
If the price is right, then get one. If not, look for a better buy.<br>
<br>
